1
00:00:56,119 --> 00:00:58,538
FINALE

2
00:01:19,142 --> 00:01:20,602
Do Eun-hyuk.

3
00:01:23,563 --> 00:01:24,773
Turn around.

4
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,416
[grunts]

5
00:01:52,634 --> 00:01:54,386
[Woo-seok] I'm going to Cheongun.

6
00:01:56,304 --> 00:01:57,304
CHA WOO-SEOK

7
00:01:57,305 --> 00:01:59,139
[phone buzzing]

8
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:00,392
HAN SEOL-AH

9
00:02:13,572 --> 00:02:14,573
POWER OFF

10
00:02:15,782 --> 00:02:17,908
[voicemail] The phone you are trying
to reach is turned off...

11
00:02:17,909 --> 00:02:19,077
CALL ENDED

12
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:23,205
[Woo-seok] Yoon Seung-jae discovered
that the men around you

13
00:02:23,206 --> 00:02:25,625
had all died after taking out insurance,

14
00:02:26,459 --> 00:02:28,085
so he got a policy for that reason.

15
00:02:28,086 --> 00:02:32,883
He was curious to see how you'd react,
and Do Eun-hyuk was egging him on.

16
00:02:33,717 --> 00:02:35,801
Do Eun-hyuk's mother
was an insurance agent,

17
00:02:35,802 --> 00:02:38,054
so he's known how insurance works
since he was young.

18
00:02:39,431 --> 00:02:42,266
Eun-hyuk told me
to take out insurance and offer it to you.

19
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:44,728
He said it was to test
if you would accept it.

20
00:02:45,896 --> 00:02:48,064
[Seol-ah] I'm not going to be
using you as bait.

21
00:02:49,065 --> 00:02:52,443
I'm the only one who can get close
without raising suspicion.

22
00:02:52,444 --> 00:02:53,819
I'll do it.

23
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:55,405
DO EUN-HYUK

24
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:00,326
DO EUN-HYE PRIVATE TUTORING EXPENSES
LIVING EXPENSES

25
00:03:00,327 --> 00:03:04,414
So until we catch the killer,
nothing is over yet.

26
00:03:28,188 --> 00:03:29,564
[groans]

27
00:03:32,442 --> 00:03:33,568
[sighs]

28
00:03:39,491 --> 00:03:41,076
So you haven't killed me yet.

29
00:03:43,912 --> 00:03:45,372
I'm still debating.

30
00:03:46,414 --> 00:03:48,917
Cha Woo-seok wasn't part of my plan.

31
00:03:53,129 --> 00:03:54,464
How did you know?

32
00:03:55,048 --> 00:03:56,174
That it was me.

33
00:03:58,593 --> 00:04:01,429
Killing someone
on a yacht and slipping away

34
00:04:03,306 --> 00:04:05,849
is easy for a diver skilled
in underwater photography.

35
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:08,186
HAN SEOL-AH

36
00:04:08,728 --> 00:04:09,728
CHA WOO-SEOK

37
00:04:09,729 --> 00:04:11,772
[phone buzzing]

38
00:04:11,773 --> 00:04:13,108
Woo-seok?

39
00:04:14,734 --> 00:04:18,947
If you hadn't met Kim Yun-ji that day,
it would have been the perfect crime.

40
00:04:20,323 --> 00:04:21,449
Am I right?

41
00:04:23,243 --> 00:04:26,287
All auctioneers have very keen eyes.

42
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,544
And that woman was just unlucky.

43
00:04:42,554 --> 00:04:43,555
What is it?

44
00:04:44,139 --> 00:04:45,264
At least make some noise.

45
00:04:45,265 --> 00:04:47,725
- I'm getting goose bumps.
- [Eun-hyuk] Did I scare you?

46
00:04:47,726 --> 00:04:51,146
I'm sorry.
I just couldn't breathe down there.

47
00:04:53,189 --> 00:04:54,190
[sighs]

48
00:04:55,525 --> 00:04:58,277
[Eun-hyuk] It feels like this is
the first time we're talking like this.

49
00:04:58,278 --> 00:04:59,362
[scoffs]

50
00:05:00,697 --> 00:05:03,825
Well, do you even talk to anyone
besides Ms. Han?

51
00:05:05,076 --> 00:05:07,746
I heard you used
to be an underwater photographer.

52
00:05:08,663 --> 00:05:10,123
How do you take photos like that?

53
00:05:11,082 --> 00:05:12,083
You need...

54
00:05:13,793 --> 00:05:17,505
professional diving gear,
and you have to practice diving too.

55
00:05:18,465 --> 00:05:19,591
Diving, huh?

56
00:05:20,341 --> 00:05:21,551
That sounds hard.

57
00:05:26,973 --> 00:05:29,517
And where do you have your studio?

58
00:05:32,437 --> 00:05:33,855
It's in Cheongun.

59
00:05:39,903 --> 00:05:41,821
[grunts]

60
00:06:10,016 --> 00:06:11,226
[gasps]

61
00:06:13,436 --> 00:06:14,813
Is there anything wrong?

62
00:06:16,689 --> 00:06:17,689
[Ms. Kim gasps]

63
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:18,817
SIU INVESTIGATOR CHA WOO-SEOK

64
00:06:20,026 --> 00:06:21,569
[Eun-hyuk] Aren't you going to get that?

65
00:06:23,113 --> 00:06:26,240
What? Did you see something
you shouldn't have?

66
00:06:26,241 --> 00:06:27,991
Stay away.

67
00:06:27,992 --> 00:06:29,535
[gasps]

68
00:06:29,536 --> 00:06:30,620
[grunts]

69
00:06:41,047 --> 00:06:42,214
She should blame herself

70
00:06:42,215 --> 00:06:44,299
for ending up as a witness,
know what I mean?

71
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,135
Bad timing.

72
00:06:46,136 --> 00:06:47,345
[scoffs]

73
00:06:48,388 --> 00:06:49,889
And what about the men?

74
00:06:50,431 --> 00:06:54,018
Were you madly in love with Han Seol-ah
but lacked the confidence?

75
00:06:55,061 --> 00:06:56,771
Is that why you killed them all?

76
00:07:02,402 --> 00:07:05,070
Shut up. Don't run your mouth
when you don't know anything.

77
00:07:05,071 --> 00:07:07,823
All of those bastards deserved to die!

78
00:07:07,824 --> 00:07:09,993
[breathing shakily]

79
00:07:10,869 --> 00:07:12,369
He called himself a doctor,

80
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:15,790
yet he gaslighted his patient
and deliberately got life insurance.

81
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:19,126
That bastard used Seol-ah's trauma.

82
00:07:19,127 --> 00:07:21,087
LIFE INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

83
00:07:23,965 --> 00:07:25,466
POLICYHOLDER: CHOI YOUNG-HO

84
00:07:34,726 --> 00:07:37,352
Seol-ah was afraid
something bad might happen again,

85
00:07:37,353 --> 00:07:39,146
so she canceled the insurance,

86
00:07:39,147 --> 00:07:42,065
but that prick didn't give up
and clung on stubbornly.

87
00:07:42,066 --> 00:07:44,736
He was just a junkie
who would shoot up his own arm.

88
00:08:02,587 --> 00:08:04,464
I saved Seol-ah from that...

89
00:08:05,048 --> 00:08:07,091
that piece of trash, Young-ho!

90
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:10,136
Why did you kill Yoon Seung-jae?

91
00:08:10,803 --> 00:08:13,889
That loser who was easily swayed
by Kim Yun-ji?

92
00:08:13,890 --> 00:08:16,391
- [Seung-jae] Get out, now!
- [Ms. Kim scoffs]

93
00:08:16,392 --> 00:08:18,603
You took out life insurance too, right?

94
00:08:19,562 --> 00:08:21,730
You will regret it.

95
00:08:21,731 --> 00:08:22,815
[Eun-hyuk] "Seiren"?

96
00:08:23,691 --> 00:08:27,362
You know, the mermaid
who lured sailors with her singing.

97
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:30,531
[sighs]

98
00:08:34,577 --> 00:08:37,497
Are you still anxious that Seol-ah
might turn down your proposal?

99
00:08:39,999 --> 00:08:41,209
She's actually...

100
00:08:42,335 --> 00:08:44,420
the beneficiary of the insurance I got.

101
00:09:23,876 --> 00:09:26,003
[grunts]

102
00:09:26,004 --> 00:09:27,964
[groans]

103
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,801
[Eun-hyuk] He was a snob
who never trusted Seol-ah from the start,

104
00:09:33,177 --> 00:09:35,430
always wondering
if she chose him for his money.

105
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:39,976
The reason he couldn't
give up on Han Seol-ah

106
00:09:41,811 --> 00:09:43,688
was because every man wanted her.

107
00:09:50,361 --> 00:09:52,655
He wanted
to take the trophy all for himself!

108
00:09:54,782 --> 00:09:57,118
[breathes heavily] A jerk like that

109
00:09:57,869 --> 00:10:00,621
is better off gone
and leaving the money behind.

110
00:10:06,377 --> 00:10:07,628
[scoffs]

111
00:10:08,296 --> 00:10:11,049
[chuckling]

112
00:10:16,804 --> 00:10:18,305
Who the hell do you think you are?

113
00:10:18,306 --> 00:10:21,017
What gives you the right to do all that?

114
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:23,477
Wasn't it your obsession with her

115
00:10:23,478 --> 00:10:26,564
that made you label those men
as trash and then kill them?

116
00:10:27,106 --> 00:10:29,400
That obsession and arrogance of yours!

117
00:10:30,193 --> 00:10:32,653
That's what made Seol-ah's life
a living hell.

118
00:10:33,321 --> 00:10:35,614
Even after seeing her suffer,
you still did that.

119
00:10:35,615 --> 00:10:37,199
You son of a bitch!

120
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,202
[breathing heavily]

121
00:10:40,244 --> 00:10:42,079
[Woo-seok breathes heavily]

122
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,831
[Woo-seok, Seol-ah breathe heavily]

123
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,793
[Eun-hyuk breathing heavily]

124
00:10:50,755 --> 00:10:52,340
I don't care what you call me...

125
00:10:53,216 --> 00:10:54,342
[breathes heavily]

126
00:10:54,842 --> 00:10:58,388
...or what title you think I need to have.

127
00:11:00,014 --> 00:11:01,182
[exhales sharply]

128
00:11:04,227 --> 00:11:06,478
[breathes heavily]

129
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:11,651
Underwater, your screams
are completely swallowed up.

130
00:11:12,443 --> 00:11:13,903
I'll end it quick and easy.

131
00:11:20,284 --> 00:11:24,455
Forty-five pounds should be enough
to keep your body from surfacing.

132
00:11:28,084 --> 00:11:31,253
- [gasps] Oh, no, no. No, no, no...
- [phone beeps]

133
00:11:31,254 --> 00:11:32,463
DETECTIVE GONG JOO-YOUNG

134
00:11:40,012 --> 00:11:41,180
CHEONGUN, WHERE LIFE IS GOOD
WELCOME TO CHEONGUN CITY

135
00:11:51,691 --> 00:11:54,318
Keep going, to the edge!

136
00:11:59,657 --> 00:12:01,241
Go ahead and shoot,

137
00:12:01,242 --> 00:12:05,204
but if you kill me, Seol-ah will find out
that you're the culprit.

138
00:12:05,705 --> 00:12:07,123
Seol-ah trusts me.

139
00:12:07,748 --> 00:12:09,583
I just need you to disappear.

140
00:12:09,584 --> 00:12:10,668
[scoffs]

141
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:13,129
Don't be so ridiculous.

142
00:12:13,754 --> 00:12:15,756
She's already suspects you.

143
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:20,052
Someone like you could never understand
what we've been through together.

144
00:12:20,678 --> 00:12:21,846
We...

145
00:12:22,763 --> 00:12:24,348
can never abandon each other.

146
00:12:25,141 --> 00:12:26,976
[scoffs]

147
00:12:28,060 --> 00:12:31,688
You could have just confessed
your feelings for her, right?

148
00:12:31,689 --> 00:12:33,523
She never even knew
how you felt about her.

149
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:37,737
Was your only goal in life just to get rid
of all the men that were ever near her?

150
00:12:38,654 --> 00:12:39,906
[sighs]

151
00:12:51,292 --> 00:12:52,292
[sighs]

152
00:12:52,293 --> 00:12:55,087
Well, I have no intention
of being Seol-ah's man.

153
00:12:55,671 --> 00:12:59,884
I'm just paying for my sins in my own way.

154
00:13:01,802 --> 00:13:03,386
Come on, jump in.

155
00:13:03,387 --> 00:13:05,723
If you can't, then I'll shoot you.

156
00:13:06,766 --> 00:13:08,308
[Seol-ah] Please don't!

157
00:13:08,309 --> 00:13:10,769
Eun-hyuk, Eun-hyuk, no.

158
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:13,396
You don't have to do this, Eun-hyuk.

159
00:13:13,397 --> 00:13:15,899
Don't do it. Put that down.

160
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:18,652
- Watch out, Seol-ah. He's dangerous!
- [Seol-ah] Please stop this now.

161
00:13:18,653 --> 00:13:20,905
I said, put that down!

162
00:13:22,823 --> 00:13:23,823
Please, Eun-hyuk.

163
00:13:23,824 --> 00:13:25,117
Come on, step back!

164
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:28,119
It's me. It's Seol-ah.

165
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,872
[Seol-ah sobs]

166
00:13:33,292 --> 00:13:34,918
Please stop this now.

167
00:13:34,919 --> 00:13:37,046
That bastard destroyed us!

168
00:13:37,672 --> 00:13:41,008
Cha Woo-seok suspected you.
That's how it all started.

169
00:13:42,093 --> 00:13:44,095
That's how we got to this point.

170
00:13:49,392 --> 00:13:51,727
So, you're just killing people for me?

171
00:13:54,063 --> 00:13:56,816
Do you really think
that I would want you to do that?

172
00:13:59,026 --> 00:14:00,444
[Eun-hyuk] Well, now,

173
00:14:01,028 --> 00:14:02,363
there's no turning back.

174
00:14:08,244 --> 00:14:09,537
Please don't!

175
00:14:19,255 --> 00:14:22,133
[Woo-seok grunts, breathes heavily]

176
00:14:22,925 --> 00:14:24,844
[gasps]

177
00:14:27,597 --> 00:14:28,847
[screams]

178
00:14:28,848 --> 00:14:30,933
[breathing heavily]

179
00:14:31,976 --> 00:14:33,060
Seol-ah!

180
00:14:35,813 --> 00:14:37,315
[exhales sharply] Seol-ah.

181
00:14:37,898 --> 00:14:39,399
Please look at me, Seol-ah.

182
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,483
Seol-ah!

183
00:14:40,484 --> 00:14:42,945
- Seol-ah... [breathes heavily]
- [sirens wailing]

184
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:55,874
Seol-ah, please open your eyes.
[breathes heavily]

185
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:58,001
Why did you do that?

186
00:14:58,002 --> 00:15:02,006
[breathes heavily] Seol-ah, Seol-ah!

187
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:06,468
- Ambulance! We need an ambulance!
- [officers] Don't move!

188
00:15:06,469 --> 00:15:07,552
- [sighs]
- [breathing heavily]

189
00:15:07,553 --> 00:15:08,721
What happened?

190
00:15:09,930 --> 00:15:12,515
She's been shot.
She's starting to black out.

191
00:15:12,516 --> 00:15:15,143
Wake up, Ms. Han Seol-ah!
[breathes heavily]

192
00:15:15,144 --> 00:15:16,270
Ms. Han!

193
00:15:16,854 --> 00:15:18,731
[Eun-hyuk breathes heavily]

194
00:15:23,819 --> 00:15:25,821
[siren wailing]

195
00:15:38,626 --> 00:15:40,294
PATIENT - CURRENT STATUS
HAN SEOL-** - IN SURGERY

196
00:15:41,212 --> 00:15:42,213
[sighs]

197
00:15:59,021 --> 00:16:00,064
[exhales sharply]

198
00:16:02,858 --> 00:16:03,859
[gasps]

199
00:16:07,113 --> 00:16:08,446
[doctor] The surgery went well.

200
00:16:08,447 --> 00:16:10,573
Rehab will be needed
due to the muscle damage,

201
00:16:10,574 --> 00:16:12,868
but she should fully recover with time.

202
00:16:13,703 --> 00:16:14,703
[sighs]

203
00:16:14,704 --> 00:16:17,623
[doctor] Miraculously,
the bullet missed the major nerves.

204
00:16:18,207 --> 00:16:21,584
Once the anesthesia wears off,
we'll check for any signs of paralysis,

205
00:16:21,585 --> 00:16:24,004
and we'll give painkillers
to reduce the pain.

206
00:16:24,714 --> 00:16:27,424
[sighs] Thank you, doctor.

207
00:16:27,425 --> 00:16:30,593
Just make sure
you get proper treatment too.

208
00:16:30,594 --> 00:16:31,721
[Woo-seok sighs]

209
00:16:37,852 --> 00:16:38,853
[sighs]

210
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:42,231
[sighs]

211
00:16:48,738 --> 00:16:50,197
[Seol-ah] Please don't!

212
00:16:58,038 --> 00:17:01,709
What is the reason
you tried to kill Cha Woo-seok?

213
00:17:13,637 --> 00:17:14,930
These men.

214
00:17:15,765 --> 00:17:17,099
You know who they are, right?

215
00:17:19,935 --> 00:17:23,189
Did Han Seol-ah order you
to have all these men killed?

216
00:18:19,495 --> 00:18:20,496
[breathes shakily]

217
00:18:43,227 --> 00:18:44,812
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

218
00:18:47,731 --> 00:18:50,024
What are you doing at someone else's desk?

219
00:18:50,025 --> 00:18:53,278
Oh, Mr. Cha asked me to bring
his laptop and a few other things.

220
00:18:53,279 --> 00:18:55,780
It's like he's trying to set up
an office at the hospital.

221
00:18:55,781 --> 00:18:58,491
I told him not to think about work
and just get some rest.

222
00:18:58,492 --> 00:18:59,869
He really doesn't listen.

223
00:19:00,494 --> 00:19:02,328
But seriously, doesn't it give you chills?

224
00:19:02,329 --> 00:19:04,539
I heard the killer is
a friend of Han Seol-ah's.

225
00:19:04,540 --> 00:19:07,208
The darkest place is under the candle.

226
00:19:07,209 --> 00:19:09,419
You never know what someone's thinking.

227
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:11,462
[sighs, inhales sharply]

228
00:19:11,463 --> 00:19:15,842
But Mr. Cha got into that car accident
last time and even got shot twice.

229
00:19:15,843 --> 00:19:17,969
Isn't this job way too dangerous?

230
00:19:17,970 --> 00:19:20,638
I was happy when I got my certification,
but... [inhales sharply]

231
00:19:20,639 --> 00:19:23,224
...I wonder if I should
think about changing jobs.

232
00:19:23,225 --> 00:19:26,060
Hey, do you really think Cha-cha
got injured on the job?

233
00:19:26,061 --> 00:19:27,145
He didn't?

234
00:19:27,146 --> 00:19:29,689
Oh, my goodness.
You're so clueless, aren't you?

235
00:19:29,690 --> 00:19:32,318
He was just trying to protect his girl.

236
00:19:33,027 --> 00:19:34,819
- What?
- "What?"

237
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:38,448
No way. I thought this case was
like the thriller Basic Instinct.

238
00:19:38,449 --> 00:19:42,870
Turns out it was a life-risking,
pure romance in the end.

239
00:19:52,463 --> 00:19:53,755
[sighs]

240
00:19:53,756 --> 00:19:54,840
Did you know?

241
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,176
The doctor said

242
00:19:58,302 --> 00:20:02,848
if it weren't for you, the bullet would
have pierced right through my heart.

243
00:20:03,766 --> 00:20:07,353
Woo-seok, you saved my life too.

244
00:20:08,395 --> 00:20:09,813
Don't do that again.

245
00:20:10,773 --> 00:20:12,191
That fear I felt...

246
00:20:13,025 --> 00:20:14,944
I never want to feel that again.

247
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:20,531
And what happened to Eun-hyuk?

248
00:20:20,532 --> 00:20:21,617
[sighs]

249
00:20:22,326 --> 00:20:24,078
I think he's still not talking.

250
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:29,750
He was the person
that knew me the best in the whole world,

251
00:20:30,417 --> 00:20:35,255
and also the only friend
who stayed by my side along with Suk-ji.

252
00:20:36,298 --> 00:20:39,593
He believed that was the only way
that he could protect you, Seol-ah,

253
00:20:40,511 --> 00:20:42,221
but he was sorely mistaken.

254
00:20:43,013 --> 00:20:44,390
I need to know.

255
00:20:44,974 --> 00:20:48,185
I really have to hear why he did it.

256
00:20:48,978 --> 00:20:50,395
Your recovery comes first.

257
00:20:50,396 --> 00:20:55,609
You can tell the police
that Han Seol-ah will turn herself in.

258
00:20:58,654 --> 00:21:00,114
I'll turn myself in.

259
00:21:01,198 --> 00:21:02,324
[sighs]

260
00:21:03,242 --> 00:21:05,202
GANGHA POLICE STATION

261
00:21:20,217 --> 00:21:25,014
TRUSTED POLICE, TOGETHER WITH THE PEOPLE
COMMITTED TO INTEGRITY AND TRANSPARENCY

262
00:21:25,931 --> 00:21:27,307
Seol-ah.

263
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:31,270
Seol-ah!

264
00:21:32,521 --> 00:21:33,771
What's Seol-ah doing here?

265
00:21:33,772 --> 00:21:35,524
Han Seol-ah turned herself in.

266
00:21:36,608 --> 00:21:40,153
She told us that she was
the one who put you up to the murders.

267
00:21:40,154 --> 00:21:41,613
So we no longer need your statement.

268
00:21:43,574 --> 00:21:46,285
No, leave Seol-ah out of this.

269
00:21:47,161 --> 00:21:48,161
I did it all.

270
00:21:48,162 --> 00:21:49,872
I killed them!

271
00:21:50,539 --> 00:21:52,457
Seol-ah had nothing to do with it!

272
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:53,875
- [Eun-gyeom grunts]
- Seol-ah...

273
00:21:53,876 --> 00:21:56,003
Seol-ah doesn't know anything!

274
00:21:57,463 --> 00:22:00,673
She is innocent! [breathes heavily]

275
00:22:00,674 --> 00:22:02,509
It wasn't Seol-ah!

276
00:22:03,469 --> 00:22:05,387
It wasn't Seol-ah!

277
00:22:07,097 --> 00:22:09,682
[screaming]

278
00:22:09,683 --> 00:22:12,519
[door opens, closes]

279
00:22:15,773 --> 00:22:17,733
[Seong-il sighs]

280
00:22:19,234 --> 00:22:21,861
What is your real reason
for going this far?

281
00:22:21,862 --> 00:22:25,574
I'd like to cross-examine him.

282
00:22:26,325 --> 00:22:28,076
[Seong-il] Then, what?

283
00:22:28,077 --> 00:22:30,329
You think that's going to make him talk?

284
00:22:32,289 --> 00:22:33,624
Maybe.

285
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:36,919
Since that's the only way
he can protect Seol-ah.

286
00:22:41,507 --> 00:22:43,342
Do Eun-hyuk's going to confess.

287
00:22:43,926 --> 00:22:45,677
He wants us to release her.

288
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:09,326
[Seong-il sighs]

289
00:23:19,086 --> 00:23:22,506
How did you find out
that Paek Jun-beom was actually Lee Su-ho?

290
00:23:32,683 --> 00:23:35,060
When I followed him to his villa,

291
00:23:36,436 --> 00:23:38,188
I got chills down my spine.

292
00:23:39,481 --> 00:23:42,276
The house was exactly
the way Lee Su-ho described it.

293
00:23:43,026 --> 00:23:45,445
He smiled
with just one corner of his mouth,

294
00:23:46,238 --> 00:23:49,282
him being left-handed,
and even the way he walked.

295
00:23:49,283 --> 00:23:51,075
- Surprise!
- Surprise!

296
00:23:51,076 --> 00:23:54,121
- [exclaims] What is this? [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Happy birthday.

297
00:23:54,955 --> 00:23:56,622
[Seol-ah] Oh, thanks.

298
00:23:56,623 --> 00:23:58,083
Happy birthday.

299
00:24:01,628 --> 00:24:02,754
[Eun-hyuk] More than anything,

300
00:24:03,714 --> 00:24:05,841
it's the way he looked at Seol-ah.

301
00:24:07,301 --> 00:24:08,969
It bothered me from the start.

302
00:24:09,553 --> 00:24:11,680
And it didn't feel unfamiliar.

303
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:23,233
I just needed a final confirmation.

304
00:24:32,492 --> 00:24:33,951
[grunts, groans]

305
00:24:33,952 --> 00:24:35,037
- Whoa.
- Oh...

306
00:24:36,121 --> 00:24:37,164
[grunts]

307
00:24:40,542 --> 00:24:41,668
[chokes]

308
00:24:42,669 --> 00:24:44,171
[Eun-hyuk] The moment
I confirmed his allergy,

309
00:24:45,172 --> 00:24:47,591
I noticed Seol-ah had figured it out too,

310
00:24:49,468 --> 00:24:52,012
and I could guess where they were headed.

311
00:25:14,743 --> 00:25:19,330
[gasps, breathes shakily]
Get off me! Let go of me!

312
00:25:19,331 --> 00:25:20,998
[sighs]

313
00:25:20,999 --> 00:25:22,834
[snickers]

314
00:25:28,090 --> 00:25:30,300
[Seol-ah, Jun-beom breathing heavily]

315
00:25:36,181 --> 00:25:37,891
INDUSTRIAL CIRCUIT BREAKER

316
00:25:47,526 --> 00:25:49,903
[both grunting]

317
00:25:54,074 --> 00:25:56,410
[Eun-hyuk groaning]

318
00:26:08,255 --> 00:26:10,257
[yelping, panting]

319
00:26:22,060 --> 00:26:23,061
[Eun-hyuk grunts]

320
00:26:23,854 --> 00:26:26,273
[grunting]

321
00:26:29,526 --> 00:26:30,527
[inhales deeply]

322
00:26:32,446 --> 00:26:33,530
[sighs]

323
00:26:34,406 --> 00:26:35,407
[sighs]

324
00:26:42,289 --> 00:26:43,332
[grunts]

325
00:26:49,379 --> 00:26:52,632
If I hadn't gone there, she could've died.

326
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:54,926
That was not murder.

327
00:26:56,219 --> 00:26:57,888
I was protecting Seol-ah.

328
00:27:04,895 --> 00:27:05,979
[sighs]

329
00:27:13,278 --> 00:27:14,488
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

330
00:27:15,572 --> 00:27:17,323
[Gong] From your overseas tuition

331
00:27:17,324 --> 00:27:20,576
to your underwater photography equipment,
and even your studio rent,

332
00:27:20,577 --> 00:27:25,791
why is it that Chair Kim Sun-ae has been
supporting you for more than a decade?

333
00:27:27,876 --> 00:27:29,961
What did you do for her in return?

334
00:27:32,005 --> 00:27:33,672
I lent Chair Kim Sun-ae my name.

335
00:27:33,673 --> 00:27:36,510
She used it to buy and sell artworks.

336
00:27:37,427 --> 00:27:40,847
- So, you just let her use your name--
- I murdered Chair Kim too.

337
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:48,896
She exploited Seol-ah
whenever she pleased,

338
00:27:48,897 --> 00:27:52,818
and then when a problem arose,
she tried to get rid of her.

339
00:28:04,830 --> 00:28:06,498
I think he's hiding something.

340
00:28:28,979 --> 00:28:31,355
I already confessed. I said I did it all.

341
00:28:31,356 --> 00:28:32,815
Please let Seol-ah go.

342
00:28:32,816 --> 00:28:34,401
She didn't even know anything.

343
00:28:36,361 --> 00:28:37,820
Could you please let us talk in private?

344
00:28:37,821 --> 00:28:40,114
- There's nothing to talk about.
- Eun-hyuk.

345
00:28:40,115 --> 00:28:41,282
Let her go already.

346
00:28:41,283 --> 00:28:43,368
Or I'm not saying another word.

347
00:28:47,622 --> 00:28:49,791
Why don't you step out for now?

348
00:28:52,169 --> 00:28:54,504
You said you did it all for me,

349
00:28:55,505 --> 00:28:57,673
and don't even have
the courage to face me?

350
00:28:57,674 --> 00:28:59,217
I said get out!

351
00:29:06,766 --> 00:29:08,685
[breathes shakily]

352
00:29:09,769 --> 00:29:11,229
[sighs]

353
00:29:23,575 --> 00:29:24,575
Are you all right?

354
00:29:24,576 --> 00:29:26,660
The cross-examination won't work.

355
00:29:26,661 --> 00:29:28,662
Do Eun-hyuk is refusing to talk.

356
00:29:28,663 --> 00:29:31,333
He doesn't want Seol-ah
to see him at his lowest.

357
00:29:36,505 --> 00:29:37,506
[sighs]

358
00:29:38,507 --> 00:29:41,009
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

359
00:29:42,511 --> 00:29:45,387
Your stomach is just fine,
so eat regularly and plenty,

360
00:29:45,388 --> 00:29:47,015
and you'll heal faster.

361
00:29:47,974 --> 00:29:49,351
You don't want it?

362
00:29:51,061 --> 00:29:53,062
Want me to wash your hair?
There's a bathroom right there.

363
00:29:53,063 --> 00:29:55,690
With your arm like this,
it must be tough, right?

364
00:29:56,233 --> 00:29:57,816
Suk-ji.

365
00:29:57,817 --> 00:29:59,401
[Suk-ji] Hmm?

366
00:29:59,402 --> 00:30:01,530
Why are you quiet about Eun-hyuk?

367
00:30:03,198 --> 00:30:04,241
Well, you know,

368
00:30:05,325 --> 00:30:06,868
I still can't believe it.

369
00:30:07,494 --> 00:30:09,286
A friend I grew up with doing that.

370
00:30:09,287 --> 00:30:11,830
I wanted to go over there
and grab him by the neck...

371
00:30:11,831 --> 00:30:16,001
Or just killing that jerk myself,
so many things crossed my mind.

372
00:30:16,002 --> 00:30:17,836
But that's not what I should be doing.

373
00:30:17,837 --> 00:30:20,173
I should be looking after you.

374
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:22,717
[knocks on door]

375
00:30:33,395 --> 00:30:34,395
You came early.

376
00:30:34,396 --> 00:30:36,814
- I thought you'd stop by later on.
- Oh...

377
00:30:36,815 --> 00:30:38,774
I just took the day off,

378
00:30:38,775 --> 00:30:41,236
and Suk-ji needs to get to her bar, so...

379
00:30:41,820 --> 00:30:44,071
I hired someone for the day shift.

380
00:30:44,072 --> 00:30:45,407
Oh, I see.

381
00:30:46,032 --> 00:30:48,200
Still, it's not the same
when the owner's not around,

382
00:30:48,201 --> 00:30:50,995
so you should get going,
don't you think? [chuckles]

383
00:30:50,996 --> 00:30:52,872
You wanted to see Seol-ah, right?

384
00:30:55,083 --> 00:30:57,294
Uh... [chuckles]

385
00:30:59,087 --> 00:31:01,089
Uh, I was worried, so...

386
00:31:07,637 --> 00:31:08,888
[chuckles]

387
00:31:12,892 --> 00:31:17,105
We know that he confessed and all,
and the evidence checks out too,

388
00:31:17,689 --> 00:31:20,190
but isn't the motive
for Chair Kim's case is a bit weak?

389
00:31:20,191 --> 00:31:23,652
Well, maybe Chair Kim knew
all about Do Eun-hyuk's weakness.

390
00:31:23,653 --> 00:31:27,072
The sum is too big
to be just payment for borrowing his name.

391
00:31:27,073 --> 00:31:28,365
Ju Hyun-su.

392
00:31:28,366 --> 00:31:29,783
He was her henchman, wasn't he?

393
00:31:29,784 --> 00:31:31,453
Could he be connected to Do Eun-hyuk?

394
00:31:36,708 --> 00:31:38,709
Come on, I can do it myself.

395
00:31:38,710 --> 00:31:40,836
[Woo-seok]
No, it's hard with just one hand.

396
00:31:40,837 --> 00:31:42,796
Well, I can ask the nurse for help too.

397
00:31:42,797 --> 00:31:45,090
Ugh. [sighs] Just trust me, okay?

398
00:31:45,091 --> 00:31:48,010
You may not believe it,
but I used to do my little sister's hair.

399
00:31:48,011 --> 00:31:50,764
Well, it's not that I don't trust you...

400
00:31:51,431 --> 00:31:52,641
Are you embarrassed?

401
00:31:53,433 --> 00:31:54,933
[scoffs] No, I'm not.

402
00:31:54,934 --> 00:31:57,895
- [chuckles]
- Fine, go ahead and do it.

403
00:31:57,896 --> 00:31:59,022
[Woo-seok inhales deeply]

404
00:32:03,735 --> 00:32:06,362
[melancholy music plays]

405
00:32:06,363 --> 00:32:08,657
[inhales deeply, grunts]

406
00:32:16,623 --> 00:32:18,499
Oh, I should've offered
to wash your hair too.

407
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:19,668
Hey...

408
00:32:28,635 --> 00:32:30,344
It's all dry now, right?

409
00:32:30,345 --> 00:32:33,306
No, uh... I'm not done yet.

410
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:36,101
[clears throat]

411
00:32:43,108 --> 00:32:47,278
Anyway, do you think
I can go back to a normal life?

412
00:32:50,490 --> 00:32:53,034
Just a simple life like everyone else's.

413
00:33:00,667 --> 00:33:01,793
Of course.

414
00:33:03,753 --> 00:33:04,796
What do you think

415
00:33:05,797 --> 00:33:09,759
if you and I just start out
like a normal couple?

416
00:33:11,261 --> 00:33:12,554
[chuckles]

417
00:33:26,609 --> 00:33:29,236
- Ow. [groans]
- Oh! [exclaims]

418
00:33:29,237 --> 00:33:31,572
- Oh! Are you okay? I'm sorry. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

419
00:33:31,573 --> 00:33:33,157
Your arm, I forgot.

420
00:33:33,158 --> 00:33:35,326
[chuckles] Yeah, it's okay. It's okay.

421
00:34:05,899 --> 00:34:08,568
EMERGENCY TRANSPORT

422
00:34:28,004 --> 00:34:33,092
Hearing that that guy got caught
made me feel even worse for Detective Cha.

423
00:34:34,052 --> 00:34:36,054
I'm not trying to blame you, okay?

424
00:34:36,888 --> 00:34:41,226
I'm just worried about
how much you must be beating yourself up.

425
00:34:41,935 --> 00:34:44,979
The truth is, I might have known
that it was insurance fraud.

426
00:34:45,563 --> 00:34:50,609
But admitting it would mean
I let it slip through my very own hands.

427
00:34:50,610 --> 00:34:54,530
So I hid behind the verdict,
telling myself, "I did what I could.

428
00:34:54,531 --> 00:34:56,156
I'm a stickler for the rules."

429
00:34:56,157 --> 00:34:57,741
Oh, honey.

430
00:34:57,742 --> 00:35:01,495
There were times when I looked
into Woo-seok's eyes,

431
00:35:01,496 --> 00:35:06,792
it felt like I could see
the truth that I'd been avoiding.

432
00:35:06,793 --> 00:35:08,002
[sighs]

433
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:10,421
Oh, sweetie,

434
00:35:11,256 --> 00:35:13,383
it must've been so hard for you.

435
00:35:15,510 --> 00:35:18,179
How about if you try to fix it now?

436
00:35:19,055 --> 00:35:23,351
The only way is to make sure
that bastard Ju Hyun-su

437
00:35:24,936 --> 00:35:26,312
gets the maximum sentence.

438
00:35:28,398 --> 00:35:29,566
That's it.

439
00:35:32,402 --> 00:35:34,821
[sighs] Finally, you're going home.

440
00:35:35,697 --> 00:35:38,992
I need to make a stop
before heading home, though.

441
00:35:41,452 --> 00:35:44,831
THE LATE CHA WOO-HEE
OCTOBER 8, 1993 - AUGUST 28, 2020

442
00:35:51,796 --> 00:35:54,381
I've always wanted to come here before.

443
00:35:54,382 --> 00:35:56,968
- [Woo-seok sighs]
- I've heard so much about her.

444
00:35:58,678 --> 00:36:03,016
After catching Ju Hyun-su,
it was harder for me to come here.

445
00:36:03,683 --> 00:36:07,562
It felt like I was the one
who needed to atone, not him.

446
00:36:08,855 --> 00:36:11,232
Don't you think your sister wants to hear

447
00:36:12,025 --> 00:36:14,819
that her brother
is finally doing okay now?

448
00:36:15,737 --> 00:36:21,200
I'm sure that she'll want to see you
smiling and living cheerfully again.

449
00:36:22,744 --> 00:36:24,786
I'll leave you alone with her now.

450
00:36:24,787 --> 00:36:26,539
Say what you never said.

451
00:36:50,688 --> 00:36:51,814
Woo-hee.

452
00:36:58,196 --> 00:36:59,530
I am...

453
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:04,369
so sorry. [sniffles]

454
00:37:04,994 --> 00:37:07,121
[sobbing]

455
00:37:14,128 --> 00:37:15,420
I was too late.

456
00:37:15,421 --> 00:37:17,507
[sobbing]

457
00:37:30,645 --> 00:37:33,105
[doorbell rings]

458
00:37:33,106 --> 00:37:34,357
[Eun-hye sighs]

459
00:37:38,778 --> 00:37:39,779
[door lock beeps]

460
00:37:47,870 --> 00:37:50,915
I just got back,
so that's all I have in the fridge.

461
00:37:52,166 --> 00:37:53,418
Tell me...

462
00:37:54,961 --> 00:37:57,296
have you visited Eun-hyuk yet?

463
00:37:57,964 --> 00:37:59,382
He's given up completely.

464
00:37:59,966 --> 00:38:03,469
He doesn't want a lawyer
and refuses to appeal.

465
00:38:05,263 --> 00:38:08,891
At some point, he started acting strange.

466
00:38:10,101 --> 00:38:14,105
And after that,
you started acting hostile toward me.

467
00:38:17,150 --> 00:38:21,737
That's because I was feeling
anxious and scared,

468
00:38:21,738 --> 00:38:24,031
wondering if my brother
had done something bad,

469
00:38:24,032 --> 00:38:27,492
or wondering what he might be planning,

470
00:38:27,493 --> 00:38:29,494
so I turned the blame toward you.

471
00:38:29,495 --> 00:38:32,205
"Everything will be fine
if Seol-ah is gone.

472
00:38:32,206 --> 00:38:34,375
It's all her fault anyway," I thought.

473
00:38:35,251 --> 00:38:37,211
On the day of Seung-jae's accident,

474
00:38:38,379 --> 00:38:40,715
I wasn't with Eun-hyuk the whole day.

475
00:38:42,008 --> 00:38:45,053
I lied to the police and even showed them

476
00:38:45,803 --> 00:38:48,263
the delivery order history
and screenshots...

477
00:38:48,264 --> 00:38:49,932
[chuckles] ...but...

478
00:38:51,017 --> 00:38:53,311
although he knew I was committing perjury,

479
00:38:54,395 --> 00:38:55,646
he didn't say anything.

480
00:38:58,524 --> 00:39:00,150
I wished it had been you.

481
00:39:00,151 --> 00:39:01,359
Han Seol-ah.

482
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,195
It's that woman who killed her.

483
00:39:03,196 --> 00:39:07,909
And that's why I tipped off the police.

484
00:39:08,451 --> 00:39:10,661
I'm sorry. [sniffles]

485
00:39:11,245 --> 00:39:12,747
I made a mistake.

486
00:39:13,873 --> 00:39:16,708
Eun-hye, you must pull yourself together.

487
00:39:16,709 --> 00:39:21,004
Life is full of difficulty,
so you have to stay strong.

488
00:39:21,005 --> 00:39:25,509
The thing is,
he's the only family I have left.

489
00:39:25,510 --> 00:39:29,222
I hate him to death,
but I feel sorry for him.

490
00:39:31,057 --> 00:39:32,224
[sniffles]

491
00:39:32,225 --> 00:39:34,018
He wants you to go see him.

492
00:39:35,436 --> 00:39:38,189
[scoffs] His life has
completely fallen apart,

493
00:39:39,524 --> 00:39:41,316
but he's still asking for you.

494
00:39:41,317 --> 00:39:43,152
Only you and no one else.

495
00:39:49,283 --> 00:39:50,326
[sighs]

496
00:40:14,058 --> 00:40:15,393
[Eun-hyuk sighs]

497
00:40:20,731 --> 00:40:24,694
So, are you finally ready?

498
00:40:28,197 --> 00:40:31,242
I know there's something
you need to tell me.

499
00:40:34,579 --> 00:40:36,330
That's why I asked you to come.

500
00:40:38,374 --> 00:40:39,375
[sighs]

501
00:40:42,879 --> 00:40:46,382
[sighs] "Where did things start
to go wrong?"

502
00:40:47,758 --> 00:40:49,969
"How did I get to this point?"

503
00:40:51,804 --> 00:40:53,639
As I thought back,

504
00:40:54,974 --> 00:40:58,686
piece by piece, it made sense.

505
00:40:59,520 --> 00:41:01,689
Everything led back to that day,

506
00:41:02,648 --> 00:41:04,859
the day I wish I would've died.

507
00:41:05,693 --> 00:41:07,904
[sorrowful music plays]

508
00:41:08,946 --> 00:41:10,697
But the small hand
you reached out to me with...

509
00:41:10,698 --> 00:41:12,824
- [Seol-ah] Get up, Do Eun-hyuk.
- [Eun-hyuk groans]

510
00:41:12,825 --> 00:41:15,286
[breathing heavily]

511
00:41:16,954 --> 00:41:20,875
...became my salvation
and my reason to keep living.

512
00:41:23,794 --> 00:41:25,463
I wanted to live.

513
00:41:27,256 --> 00:41:28,257
[sighs]

514
00:41:29,133 --> 00:41:31,093
I just wanted to live.

515
00:41:31,677 --> 00:41:34,304
- [sobbing] Go away!
- [parent] Get back here, you brat!

516
00:41:34,305 --> 00:41:37,807
- How dare you! You little...
- Go away! [screams]

517
00:41:37,808 --> 00:41:39,101
[parent exclaims]

518
00:41:46,442 --> 00:41:48,069
[Eun-hyuk breathes shakily]

519
00:41:50,279 --> 00:41:51,864
I just wanted to live, you know?

520
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:56,160
But my father died.

521
00:41:57,411 --> 00:41:59,537
It was ruled an accidental fall,

522
00:41:59,538 --> 00:42:01,999
and no one ever knew
I was the one who did it,

523
00:42:02,875 --> 00:42:04,585
but maybe my mom knew?

524
00:42:05,586 --> 00:42:07,755
[panting] Where did I put it?

525
00:42:10,591 --> 00:42:12,260
GW LIFE INSURANCE
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

526
00:42:13,219 --> 00:42:15,470
Mom! [sobs]

527
00:42:15,471 --> 00:42:16,972
Where are you going?

528
00:42:16,973 --> 00:42:18,432
Mom!

529
00:42:19,976 --> 00:42:21,476
Mom, wait!

530
00:42:21,477 --> 00:42:22,687
Mom.

531
00:42:23,396 --> 00:42:26,857
[Eun-hyuk] All she took was the life
insurance payout from my father's death,

532
00:42:27,608 --> 00:42:29,277
and she never came back.

533
00:42:33,197 --> 00:42:34,782
That's when I learned

534
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:40,121
that someone's death
can be turned into money.

535
00:42:40,746 --> 00:42:45,209
I also learned
that it can be quietly buried too.

536
00:42:47,253 --> 00:42:52,383
And your parents got their insurance
through my mom too.

537
00:42:55,303 --> 00:42:58,347
Wait. How did you know?

538
00:43:00,016 --> 00:43:01,225
It was me.

539
00:43:02,226 --> 00:43:03,602
I started the fire.

540
00:43:05,563 --> 00:43:07,356
[breathes shakily]

541
00:43:13,487 --> 00:43:15,280
That can't be. [breathes shakily]

542
00:43:15,281 --> 00:43:16,573
I know I was...

543
00:43:16,574 --> 00:43:18,700
I was holding the lighter...

544
00:43:18,701 --> 00:43:20,411
[breathes shakily]

545
00:43:22,788 --> 00:43:23,997
[Eun-hyuk] You passed out.

546
00:43:23,998 --> 00:43:26,292
[breathing heavily]

547
00:43:27,793 --> 00:43:29,085
[gasps]

548
00:43:29,086 --> 00:43:30,503
[breathes heavily]

549
00:43:30,504 --> 00:43:33,924
Seol-ah. Seol-ah, wake up.
Wake up, Seol-ah...

550
00:44:09,043 --> 00:44:10,419
[grunts]

551
00:44:13,422 --> 00:44:15,215
- It wasn't you.
- [grunts]

552
00:44:15,216 --> 00:44:16,634
It was me.

553
00:44:17,385 --> 00:44:22,515
Because I thought that if you got
the insurance payout,

554
00:44:23,849 --> 00:44:25,935
your parents' sacrifice
wouldn't be in vain.

555
00:44:26,685 --> 00:44:27,686
[sighs]

556
00:44:28,354 --> 00:44:32,608
[Eun-hyuk] Even as I watched you suffer
your whole life because of a false memory,

557
00:44:33,484 --> 00:44:35,778
I didn't have the courage to tell you.

558
00:44:36,570 --> 00:44:39,198
The moment I caused my father's death,

559
00:44:40,282 --> 00:44:42,201
I became a monster.

560
00:44:42,785 --> 00:44:47,581
And after I set fire to your house,
I could no longer get close to you.

561
00:44:48,874 --> 00:44:51,335
At Suk-ji's bar, you said you had hopes

562
00:44:51,919 --> 00:44:55,923
for our relationship
once you and I became adults.

563
00:44:58,342 --> 00:44:59,593
Hearing that...

564
00:45:01,887 --> 00:45:03,681
made me so happy and...

565
00:45:05,724 --> 00:45:07,600
sad at the same time.

566
00:45:07,601 --> 00:45:08,686
[sighs]

567
00:45:10,104 --> 00:45:13,691
I've ruined the future we could have had
with my own hands.

568
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,952
[breathes heavily]

569
00:45:35,087 --> 00:45:38,173
Chair Kim saw all of that... [sighs]

570
00:45:38,174 --> 00:45:42,094
...and after that, I became her lapdog.

571
00:45:53,522 --> 00:45:57,735
That woman knew exactly
what I feared the most in life.

572
00:45:59,195 --> 00:46:00,862
[Chair Kim]
Ju Hyun-su is getting out soon.

573
00:46:00,863 --> 00:46:03,239
Take care of that bastard quietly.

574
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,782
If you fail,

575
00:46:04,783 --> 00:46:09,997
that bitch is going to learn the secret
that you fear more than your own death.

576
00:46:18,130 --> 00:46:20,633
[humming]

577
00:46:33,437 --> 00:46:35,231
I did all of that.

578
00:46:36,148 --> 00:46:40,319
You need to let go of your guilt
and stop hurting yourself.

579
00:46:40,986 --> 00:46:42,529
I'll take all the punishment.

580
00:46:42,530 --> 00:46:44,614
You said it yourself.

581
00:46:44,615 --> 00:46:47,451
No one gets to choose the parents
that they get in life.

582
00:46:48,077 --> 00:46:49,912
The abuse you went through,

583
00:46:50,496 --> 00:46:54,416
and me ending up an orphan,
it was not our fault.

584
00:46:55,251 --> 00:46:58,002
But how we moved forward
after that was up to us.

585
00:46:58,003 --> 00:46:59,547
That was our choice.

586
00:47:00,839 --> 00:47:04,759
I was in a lot of pain too,
but I learned to accept my life.

587
00:47:04,760 --> 00:47:08,514
You had the chance
to make different choices many times.

588
00:47:10,516 --> 00:47:14,019
By the time I realized it...
[sighs] ...it was too late.

589
00:47:14,812 --> 00:47:18,607
I had no choice
but to continue down the path I was on.

590
00:47:19,316 --> 00:47:22,111
You're the one who made me
the most miserable.

591
00:47:28,367 --> 00:47:29,450
Seol-ah.

592
00:47:29,451 --> 00:47:30,661
[Seol-ah] Don't ever...

593
00:47:32,162 --> 00:47:33,831
say my name again.

594
00:47:39,169 --> 00:47:40,546
[breathes shakily]

595
00:47:51,223 --> 00:47:52,850
[door closes]

596
00:48:31,013 --> 00:48:33,015
[sobbing]

597
00:48:35,517 --> 00:48:36,518
[sighs]

598
00:49:36,245 --> 00:49:37,286
DRAWING THE MIND

599
00:49:37,287 --> 00:49:39,373
[children chattering indistinctly]

600
00:49:46,088 --> 00:49:47,798
DRAWING THE MIND: ART THERAPY PROGRAM
WITH NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

601
00:49:58,767 --> 00:50:00,601
Hey, here's a gift for you.

602
00:50:00,602 --> 00:50:01,812
[colleague] Hello.

603
00:50:02,730 --> 00:50:03,856
Wow!

604
00:50:06,150 --> 00:50:07,526
Hi, mister.

605
00:50:08,068 --> 00:50:10,028
Chae-rin! How have you been?

606
00:50:10,821 --> 00:50:11,904
How you been feeling?

607
00:50:11,905 --> 00:50:14,031
I'm not in much pain anymore.

608
00:50:14,032 --> 00:50:16,368
And today, I'm here as a helper.

609
00:50:17,077 --> 00:50:18,120
Can you do a good job?

610
00:50:19,288 --> 00:50:20,706
[chuckles]

611
00:50:21,707 --> 00:50:23,624
So then I look forward
to working with you.

612
00:50:23,625 --> 00:50:25,460
- Me too.
- Here, take this.

613
00:50:25,461 --> 00:50:27,087
How have you been?

614
00:50:38,932 --> 00:50:40,768
She's still at the shelter, isn't she?

615
00:50:42,478 --> 00:50:46,815
Mm-hmm. She still goes
to the hospital often, so it's not easy.

616
00:50:51,487 --> 00:50:52,613
[sighs]

617
00:50:54,198 --> 00:50:59,118
DRAWING THE MIND

618
00:50:59,119 --> 00:51:03,498
All right, kids, today you're going
to create a new story, your story.

619
00:51:03,499 --> 00:51:05,875
Don't think about the darkness
from your past.

620
00:51:05,876 --> 00:51:08,920
Instead, imagine the person
you'd like to become,

621
00:51:08,921 --> 00:51:12,507
and let your imagination run free on
the paper you have right in front of you.

622
00:51:12,508 --> 00:51:14,301
[children] Okay!

623
00:51:14,885 --> 00:51:16,553
Shall we get started?

624
00:51:23,769 --> 00:51:24,812
[child] Look at this.

625
00:51:34,154 --> 00:51:35,238
Try this color.

626
00:51:35,239 --> 00:51:37,324
Thank you, Chae-rin.

627
00:51:48,377 --> 00:51:50,461
I see that you like the color blue.

628
00:51:50,462 --> 00:51:53,590
Yeah, because it reminds me of the sky.

629
00:51:59,763 --> 00:52:00,889
That must've been painful.

630
00:52:05,352 --> 00:52:08,354
You know, when I draw, it doesn't hurt.

631
00:52:08,355 --> 00:52:10,523
It makes me forget about that time.

632
00:52:10,524 --> 00:52:12,109
Really?

633
00:52:13,110 --> 00:52:14,318
I felt the same way.

634
00:52:14,319 --> 00:52:18,406
That's why I drew,
did wood carving, and things like that.

635
00:52:18,407 --> 00:52:20,908
[Chae-rin] Then I'm going
to keep drawing too.

636
00:52:20,909 --> 00:52:22,536
It's so much fun.

637
00:52:23,161 --> 00:52:27,039
Yeah, keep it up, and someday
we can have an exhibition together.

638
00:52:27,040 --> 00:52:28,292
Really?

639
00:52:30,961 --> 00:52:31,962
I promise.

640
00:52:32,713 --> 00:52:33,714
[chuckles]

641
00:52:43,390 --> 00:52:44,391
[Woo-seok chuckles]

642
00:53:00,198 --> 00:53:02,867
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

643
00:53:02,868 --> 00:53:06,829
At the SI Unit, we never move
unless we have information

644
00:53:06,830 --> 00:53:10,833
because lies always leave a trace.

645
00:53:10,834 --> 00:53:13,044
[scoffs] This is ridiculous.

646
00:53:13,045 --> 00:53:16,172
I told you my neck won't move
and I can't use my arm either.

647
00:53:16,173 --> 00:53:17,381
Are you refusing to pay me?

648
00:53:17,382 --> 00:53:21,385
[sighs] Mr. Koo, your acting is terrible.
I just can't get into it.

649
00:53:21,386 --> 00:53:22,678
All right, let's try that again.

650
00:53:22,679 --> 00:53:23,888
Okay.

651
00:53:23,889 --> 00:53:25,182
Phew.

652
00:53:25,849 --> 00:53:28,809
Hey, you! You damn kid.

653
00:53:28,810 --> 00:53:30,311
How dare you call me a liar?

654
00:53:30,312 --> 00:53:32,855
I'm sure everyone thinks
you've got no manners.

655
00:53:32,856 --> 00:53:35,274
Don't you dare open
your mouth without proof!

656
00:53:35,275 --> 00:53:37,777
Were you just saying
whatever you wanted to me?

657
00:53:37,778 --> 00:53:40,112
Mr. Cha, I can't do this. I'm scared!

658
00:53:40,113 --> 00:53:41,948
Oh, man, you're way too weak.

659
00:53:41,949 --> 00:53:44,743
Real situations are worse than that. Huh?

660
00:53:45,327 --> 00:53:46,661
Geez, you scared me!

661
00:53:46,662 --> 00:53:50,665
[chuckles] Wow,
you've still got quick reflexes, huh?

662
00:53:50,666 --> 00:53:53,626
Hey, Cha-cha, this is just practice.

663
00:53:53,627 --> 00:53:55,544
Why are you treating it
like the real thing?

664
00:53:55,545 --> 00:53:57,046
See that?

665
00:53:57,047 --> 00:54:00,425
Even if a fraudster lies
with their mouth, their body can't lie.

666
00:54:01,009 --> 00:54:03,719
Wow. Grim Reaper Cha never disappoints.

667
00:54:03,720 --> 00:54:04,930
I should take notes.

668
00:54:08,767 --> 00:54:10,811
Mr. Cha, someone is here to see you.

669
00:54:11,687 --> 00:54:12,729
Me?

670
00:54:17,484 --> 00:54:18,860
[Seong-il sighs]

671
00:54:20,028 --> 00:54:21,029
[smacks lips]

672
00:54:21,571 --> 00:54:23,281
Ju Hyun-su's verdict is out.

673
00:54:24,032 --> 00:54:25,283
I read the article.

674
00:54:25,784 --> 00:54:27,244
He got 15 years.

675
00:54:28,578 --> 00:54:32,082
I'm sorry, that was the maximum sentence.

676
00:54:37,295 --> 00:54:40,965
I know it's too late,
but I figured I'd only earn the right

677
00:54:40,966 --> 00:54:44,094
to apologize to you
after his sentence was finalized.

678
00:54:47,097 --> 00:54:49,558
I have no excuse for leaving you
to fight alone,

679
00:54:51,018 --> 00:54:54,730
neither as a detective, nor as a friend.

680
00:54:55,856 --> 00:54:56,940
[sighs]

681
00:55:01,153 --> 00:55:02,279
Thank you

682
00:55:03,739 --> 00:55:05,073
for your apology.

683
00:55:11,913 --> 00:55:14,540
I heard from Detective Gong
that you're on a case

684
00:55:14,541 --> 00:55:16,460
where they paid out $2.5 million.

685
00:55:17,085 --> 00:55:18,253
Yeah, why do you ask?

686
00:55:19,087 --> 00:55:20,589
The call records of the deceased.

687
00:55:22,007 --> 00:55:24,176
One name appears in all of them.

688
00:55:29,056 --> 00:55:30,682
CALL LOG

689
00:55:51,495 --> 00:55:53,497
- [door lock beeping]
- [Seol-ah] Mmm.

690
00:56:00,921 --> 00:56:02,254
There you are.

691
00:56:02,255 --> 00:56:04,174
I grabbed some groceries on the way.

692
00:56:05,509 --> 00:56:06,968
Cucumbers and...

693
00:56:07,552 --> 00:56:08,637
Some eggs.

694
00:56:10,347 --> 00:56:12,808
Carrots and also...

695
00:56:14,267 --> 00:56:15,309
some fruit.

696
00:56:15,310 --> 00:56:17,269
I noticed there was no fruit
in the fridge.

697
00:56:17,270 --> 00:56:19,146
Oh, you're very observant.

698
00:56:19,147 --> 00:56:21,525
Oh, it comes with the job.

699
00:56:22,818 --> 00:56:24,986
- Did you make kimchi stew?
- Yeah. Wanna taste it?

700
00:56:32,410 --> 00:56:33,411
How is it?

701
00:56:34,162 --> 00:56:35,704
Ugh.

702
00:56:35,705 --> 00:56:37,748
[chuckling]

703
00:56:37,749 --> 00:56:39,792
- I'm just kidding.
- Watch out.

704
00:56:39,793 --> 00:56:41,210
- I was messing with you.
- I have a weapon.

705
00:56:41,211 --> 00:56:43,921
- Whoa. I said I was just messing with you.
- [chuckles]

706
00:56:43,922 --> 00:56:46,174
Hey, it's really good.
It's perfectly seasoned.

707
00:56:48,343 --> 00:56:51,721
I never thought I would make myself
a warm meal like this.

708
00:56:52,389 --> 00:56:54,598
You've spent all these years
focused on only work.

709
00:56:54,599 --> 00:56:57,309
You should start taking better care
of yourself now.

710
00:56:57,310 --> 00:56:59,103
[chuckles]

711
00:56:59,104 --> 00:57:02,107
Says the person
who's even more of a workaholic than me.

712
00:57:03,108 --> 00:57:04,526
- [chuckles]
- [Seol-ah chuckles]

713
00:57:31,428 --> 00:57:32,846
And this is for you.

714
00:57:36,141 --> 00:57:40,645
Han Seol-ah deserves to be
way happier than anyone else.

715
00:57:43,190 --> 00:57:44,524
Can you please allow me

716
00:57:46,359 --> 00:57:47,819
to make you happy?

717
00:57:55,660 --> 00:57:57,329
I can't accept this.

718
00:57:58,580 --> 00:58:01,541
Honestly, I'm getting ready
to study abroad.

719
00:58:02,209 --> 00:58:03,834
It's an art therapy course

720
00:58:03,835 --> 00:58:07,380
for helping children
who've been hurt heal through art.

721
00:58:08,048 --> 00:58:10,842
And I have no idea how long it'll take.

722
00:58:12,010 --> 00:58:13,428
[sighing]

723
00:58:18,558 --> 00:58:20,268
[sighs]

724
00:58:27,943 --> 00:58:29,653
Please accept this anyway.

725
00:58:30,654 --> 00:58:32,155
Who said you can't go?

726
00:58:32,656 --> 00:58:34,199
Do it. Go for it.

727
00:58:36,159 --> 00:58:37,452
I'll wait for you.

728
00:58:39,204 --> 00:58:40,579
How can I do that to you?

729
00:58:40,580 --> 00:58:42,206
I can take a vacation and come see you.

730
00:58:42,207 --> 00:58:43,958
If you want me to fly over, I will.

731
00:58:43,959 --> 00:58:46,127
If you want me to wait, then I'll wait.

732
00:58:49,297 --> 00:58:53,092
Oh, actually, let's go together.
I can come with you.

733
00:58:53,093 --> 00:58:56,720
I'll take a sabbatical from work
so I can take care of you full-time.

734
00:58:56,721 --> 00:58:57,806
[chuckles]

735
00:58:58,723 --> 00:58:59,724
[chuckles]

736
00:59:02,310 --> 00:59:04,062
Whatever choice you do make...

737
00:59:06,106 --> 00:59:07,440
I'll be by your side.

738
00:59:16,825 --> 00:59:18,576
Try trusting me once.

739
00:59:20,412 --> 00:59:21,871
I already do.

740
00:59:23,581 --> 00:59:26,042
What? And you were planning
to go without me?

741
00:59:29,462 --> 00:59:31,631
I thought it'd be too selfish
of me to ask.

742
00:59:32,299 --> 00:59:35,927
It's okay. You can be selfish.

743
00:59:36,428 --> 00:59:38,054
Be as stubborn as you like.

744
00:59:39,681 --> 00:59:43,101
Whatever you do, I know I can handle it.

745
00:59:45,020 --> 00:59:46,438
'Cause after all,

746
00:59:47,605 --> 00:59:48,940
we only have each other.

747
00:59:49,983 --> 00:59:53,903
I'll be the only family
that you'll ever need.

748
00:59:55,905 --> 00:59:57,198
I promise you.

749
01:00:25,518 --> 01:00:27,019
[Seol-ah] This painting you see here

750
01:00:27,020 --> 01:00:31,315
has been on display in Royal Auction's
exhibition hall for a really long time.

751
01:00:31,316 --> 01:00:36,153
The world often labels
those who endure in silence as monsters,

752
01:00:36,154 --> 01:00:38,822
but there is so much more to every story,

753
01:00:38,823 --> 01:00:43,536
and the siren is a symbol
of temptation and destruction.

754
01:00:44,829 --> 01:00:46,914
Just ask yourself this question,

755
01:00:46,915 --> 01:00:49,167
isn't prejudice the real monster here?

756
01:00:49,876 --> 01:00:55,256
Those who refuse to see the truth
and judge someone for their past.

757
01:00:55,757 --> 01:00:59,386
That's exactly what drags
a person deeper into the water.

758
01:01:01,888 --> 01:01:05,600
Now, I see the siren
not as a creature that destroys others,

759
01:01:06,101 --> 01:01:11,940
but as a survivor who defended her voice
against prejudice until the very end.

760
01:01:14,150 --> 01:01:17,570
If you are crossing such a sea right now,

761
01:01:18,446 --> 01:01:23,826
I hope that you never lose
your own voice along the way.

762
01:01:23,827 --> 01:01:25,787
ROYAL AUCTION
CHIEF AUCTIONEER HAN SEOL-AH

763
01:01:36,423 --> 01:01:37,590
Here.

764
01:01:38,258 --> 01:01:40,300
I'll hand this over to you, Sang-mi.

765
01:01:40,301 --> 01:01:41,511
Yes, Ms. Han.

766
01:01:42,345 --> 01:01:43,595
Thank you.

767
01:01:43,596 --> 01:01:45,889
Thank you all for everything.

768
01:01:45,890 --> 01:01:47,683
We can contact you, right?

769
01:01:47,684 --> 01:01:49,144
Of course.

770
01:01:50,019 --> 01:01:51,271
Take care of yourself.

771
01:02:50,121 --> 01:02:51,498
[Woo-seok] There was a woman

772
01:02:52,123 --> 01:02:54,459
that the world once labeled as a witch.

773
01:02:56,544 --> 01:02:58,671
People condemned her recklessly...

774
01:02:59,756 --> 01:03:00,756
A FAMILY
BY HAN JIN-WOO

775
01:03:00,757 --> 01:03:02,258
...and threw stones far too easily.

776
01:03:04,093 --> 01:03:05,803
Which side are you on?

777
01:03:07,138 --> 01:03:10,600
Are you the one being pelted,
or the one throwing the stones?

778
01:03:12,560 --> 01:03:18,191
Sometimes, the truth can be cruel,
and some wounds never fully heal.

779
01:03:21,152 --> 01:03:22,820
Even so, don't give up.

780
01:03:24,322 --> 01:03:25,698
And keep loving.

781
01:03:27,784 --> 01:03:29,786
My witch still cries sometimes,

782
01:03:31,079 --> 01:03:32,163
but we're together.

783
01:03:34,249 --> 01:03:35,667
There's no salvation.

784
01:03:37,335 --> 01:03:38,503
Only that

785
01:03:39,546 --> 01:03:42,924
we refuse to let go of each other's hands.
